 for bestpractices and # Billing & Pricing Page

## Overview
Build a complete, production-ready Billing & Pricing experience for Archject that displays current plan details, seat usage, invoices & receipts, payment methods, promo codes/credits, and upgrade/downgrade flows. Also implement a connected Settings & Team Management section at the studio level to manage branding, team roles, subscription settings, and integration links that tie into billing. The deliverable should include frontend UI, backend APIs, data models, security, validation, and integration instructions sufficient for an AI development tool or engineering team to implement end-to-end.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A single workspace area (accessible from the studio sidebar) where admins/owners view and manage their subscription and billing for Archject. It consolidates: current plan summary, upgrade/downgrade pricing tiers and comparisons, invoices and downloadable receipts, payment methods (securely add / remove / set default), promo code/credits application, and trial/upgrade CTA. It is tightly coupled with the Studio Settings & Team Management page for role-based access and branding (invoices, emails) and optionally with future payment provider integrations.

Goals:
- Provide transparent subscription information and clear upgrade/downgrade paths for studios.
- Allow secure management of payment methods and easy retrieval of historical invoices and receipts.
- Support promo codes and account credits, show seat counts and next billing date.
- Surface trial status and easy upgrade from trial to paid plans.
- Ensure branding and email template controls from Settings reflect on invoice PDFs and transactional emails.

Connected features:
- Settings & Team Management: for subscription ownership, billing contact, branding (logo on invoice), email templates and who can manage billing (roles).
- User roles & permissions system (only Owners/Finance/Admin can manage billing).
- Payment provider integration (placeholder now; exact provider TBD — implement a clean payment-provider adapter).
- Accounting export: invoice download (PDF/CSV) and transaction metadata for exports.

UI elements & visual guidance:
- Page layout follows project design system: left sidebar navigation, topbar, main content area on #F7F7F9 background, cards on #FFFFFF with subtle shadow and #E5E7EB borders.
- Key sections (each in a card):
  1. Current Plan Summary card: plan name, seats used/allocated, next billing date, billing cycle, per-seat cost (if applicable), status pill (active/trial/cancelled) in status colors. Right aligned primary CTA: Upgrade / Manage seats.
  2. Pricing Tiers card: Tier grid with comparison table (features rows, columns per tier), primary CTA per tier (Upgrade/Choose). Highlight current tier with accent color border.
  3. Invoices & Receipts card: searchable & paginated table/list with invoice number, date, amount, status (paid/failed/refunded), download invoice PDF button and a "View details" expand/collapse. Allow filter by year and export CSV.
  4. Payment Methods card: list of cards on file with brand icon, last4, expiration, default badge; Add Payment Method button (opens modal/stripe-hosted element or tokenized form). Remove with confirmation, set default flow.
  5. Promo Codes & Credits card: input to apply promo codes, list of active credits, credit balance, and UI that shows how credits are applied to next invoice.
  6. Billing Contact & Billing Address card: editable fields for billing email, company name, address — used to populate invoices. Save button and validation.
  7. Trial Status / Upgrade CTA banner: top area that shows trial remaining days and "Upgrade Now" button; or if past due, a warning state with restore payment CTA.

API integrations:
- Provide an abstract payment provider adapter layer for card tokenization, subscription management, invoice retrieval and webhooks. No concrete provider is mandated; design for Stripe-like APIs but keep adapter hooks documented so provider can be swapped.
- Email generation/invoice rendering: invoice PDFs generated server-side using invoice template that pulls studio branding from Settings (logo, color accent optionally) and billing contact data.
- Webhooks endpoint to receive payment events (invoice.paid, payment_failed, subscription_updated) from the payment provider. Webhook handler updates invoice and subscription records and notifies studio members as appropriate.

## Components to Build
1. BillingPage (main container)
   - Subcomponents: CurrentPlanCard, PricingTiersGrid, InvoicesList, PaymentMethodsList, PromoCreditsCard, BillingContactForm, TrialBanner.
2. BillingModals
   - AddPaymentMethodModal (hosted element/iframe option), ConfirmRemoveCardModal, UpgradeConfirmModal, ApplyPromoModal, InvoiceDetailModal.
3. Settings & Team Management Page (studio-level)
   - Subcomponents: BrandingPanel (logo upload, invoice template preview, email template editor), TeamRolesTable (invite/remove/edit roles/permissions), SubscriptionManagementPanel (link to BillingPage, list of subscriptions), IntegrationsPanel (connectors list with enable/disable).
4. Payment Provider Adapter
   - Interfaces: createPaymentMethod, attachPaymentMethodToCustomer, detachPaymentMethod, listPaymentMethods, createSubscription, updateSubscription, listInvoices, getInvoicePdf, applyCoupon/promo.
5. Backend Webhook Receiver & Queue Processor
   - Webhook routes, signature verification, event handlers that update DB and enqueue notification emails.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Tech stack expectations: React + TypeScript, component library alignment to design tokens (spacing, colors, typography). Use CSS-in-JS (styled-components/emotion) or Tailwind with a design token layer. All components fully responsive and accessible (WCAG AA).
- Pages/Routes:
  - /studio/:studioId/billing — Billing & Pricing Page (only accessible for studio admins/owners)
  - /studio/:studioId/settings/team — Settings & Team Management
- UI Elements & Interactions:
  - Current Plan Summary: small card with plan badge, seats usage progress bar (with percentage and numeric: e.g., 8/10 seats), next billing date, "Change plan" button.
  - Pricing Tiers: responsive three-column card layout for tiers (e.g., Free, Pro, Studio). Each tile shows price (monthly/annual toggle), key features, seat limits, CTA. Tier comparison modal displays a feature matrix.
  - Invoices Table: columns [Invoice #, Date, Amount, Status, Actions]. Actions: Download PDF, View details, Resend to billing email. Table supports search by invoice number, filter by year, and pagination.
  - Payment Methods: card list with brand icons; Add card uses secure provider element (PCI compliance). Mark a card as default; removal requires confirmation if default.
  - Promo Codes: free text input + Apply button; validates with backend and shows success/failure messaging. Show available credits and how many will be applied to next invoice.
  - Modals: accessible focus trap, close on ESC, labelled with aria attributes.
  - Notifications: success/error toasts on actions (apply promo, card added, invoice downloaded).
- Visual & micro-interactions: hover lifts, focus rings, disabled states; use defined palette and spacing.

### Backend
- Tech stack expectations: Node.js/TypeScript (Express or Fastify) or equivalent. Database relational (Postgres) or document store (Postgres recommended). Use migrations and typed models (Prisma/TypeORM).
- API surface:
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/billing — return aggregated billing summary (plan, seats, next billing date, trial status, credit balance).
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/invoices?year=&page=&perPage= — paginated invoices list.
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/invoices/:invoiceId/pdf — download PDF.
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods — create/attach payment method (accepts provider token).
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods — list payment methods.
  - DELETE /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods/:methodId — detach method.
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/subscription — create or change subscription (payload: planId, seats, promoCode).
  - PATCH /api/studios/:studioId/subscription — change seats/plan.
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/promos/apply — validate and apply promo.
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/billing/contact — update billing contact & address.
  - POST /webhooks/payment-provider — webhook entrypoint for payment provider events.
- Server functions:
  - Invoice PDF generation service (render invoice with studio branding).
  - Subscription lifecycle manager (create/update/cancel subscriptions).
  - Payment provider adapter / service (abstract layer with implementations).
  - Notification service (send billing emails using email templates from Branding settings).
  - Scheduler to create recurring invoices or reconcile failed payments (if provider doesn't auto-manage).
- Data retention & logs for audit: store transaction ids, provider event ids and raw payloads.

### Integration
- Payment provider adapter contract must be defined and used by subscription APIs. Implement a mock adapter for development and a Stripe-like adapter for production.
- Webhooks: verify signature header (provider-specific) and map events to local models. On invoice.payment_succeeded => mark invoice paid, notify billing email, store pdf link. On payment_failed => set subscription/pending state and notify owners.
- Branding: the invoice PDF generator must fetch studio branding (logo/secondary color and billing contact) from Settings. Email templates should be populated with invoice links and trial/plan details.
- Team Roles: Settings page manages who can access / manage billing. Enforce via backend authorization checks on every billing endpoint.

## User Experience Flow
1. Admin navigates to Studio > Billing.
2. Top banner shows trial status or active subscription summary with "Upgrade" CTA.
3. Admin reviews Current Plan card to confirm seats and next billing date.
4. Admin opens Pricing Tiers to compare options (monthly/annual toggle). Chooses a tier and clicks "Upgrade".
5. Upgrade flow:
   - If no payment method: prompt Add Payment Method modal (secure tokenized element). After adding, create subscription via backend adapter and show success toast.
   - If payment method exists: confirm upgrade modal showing pro-rated cost/next invoice. Confirm calls subscription API, updates DB, and redirects to success state.
6. Admin manages Payment Methods: adds/removes/toggles default. Removing default prompts to select alternative or shows warning.
7. Admin views Invoices list: filters and downloads PDF, or clicks "Resend invoice" to email billing contact.
8. Admin applies a promo code via Promo card and sees credits reflected immediately in Billing Summary; next invoice will show credit deduction.
9. Non-owner user without billing permission sees read-only billing summary and "Request change" button to contact Owners.
10. Any external payment events (webhooks) update subscription and invoice state in real time; UI reflects changes with notifications.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models:

Studio
- id: UUID
- name: string
- billingContactId: UUID -> BillingContact
- defaultCurrency: string (e.g., "USD")
- branding: { logoUrl: string, invoiceAccentColor?: string, invoiceTemplateId?: UUID }
- createdAt, updatedAt

BillingContact
- id: UUID
- studioId: UUID
- name: string
- email: string
- companyName?: string
- address: { line1, line2, city, state, postalCode, country }
- taxId?: string

Subscription
- id: UUID
- studioId: UUID
- providerSubscriptionId: string (provider-specific)
- planId: string (internal plan slug)
- seats: integer
- status: enum (active, trialing, canceled, past_due, unpaid)
- pricePerSeatCents: integer
- billingCycle: enum (monthly, annual)
- nextBillingDate: timestamp
- trialEndsAt?: timestamp
- createdAt, updatedAt

Invoice
- id: UUID
- studioId: UUID
- providerInvoiceId: string
- invoiceNumber: string
- amountDueCents: integer
- amountPaidCents: integer
- currency: string
- status: enum (draft, open, paid, void, failed)
- pdfUrl?: string or blob storage key
- issuedAt: timestamp
- dueAt?: timestamp
- lineItems: JSON array [{description, quantity, unitAmountCents}]
- rawProviderPayload: JSON
- createdAt, updatedAt

PaymentMethod
- id: UUID
- studioId: UUID
- providerPaymentMethodId: string
- brand: string (Visa, Mastercard)
- last4: string
- expMonth: int
- expYear: int
- isDefault: boolean
- createdAt, updatedAt

Promo / Credit
- id: UUID
- code: string
- studioId?: UUID (if single-use per studio)
- amountCents?: integer
- percentOff?: integer
- expiresAt?: timestamp
- isActive: boolean
- appliedToInvoiceIds: JSON array
- createdAt, updatedAt

WebhookEvents
- id: UUID
- providerEventId: string
- studioId?: UUID
- eventType: string
- payload: JSON
- receivedAt, processedAt, status

- API Endpoints: (all require Authorization: Bearer <token> and studio-level permission check)
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/billing [200] — returns consolidated billing summary (Subscription, credits, default payment method)
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/subscription [200] — subscription details
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/subscription [201] — create/upgrade (body: planId, seats, paymentMethodId?, promoCode?)
  - PATCH /api/studios/:studioId/subscription [200] — update (planId?, seats?)
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/subscription/cancel [200] — cancel subscription
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/invoices [200] — list invoices (query: page, perPage, year, status)
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/invoices/:invoiceId [200] — invoice detail
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/invoices/:invoiceId/pdf [200] — stream PDF
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/invoices/:invoiceId/resend [200] — resend to billing contact
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods [200] — list
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods [201] — create (body: providerToken)
  - DELETE /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods/:methodId [204]
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods/:methodId/default [200]
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/promos/apply [200] — apply promo (body: code)
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/billing/contact [200] — update billing contact
  - POST /webhooks/payment-provider [200] — receive provider events

- Security:
  - Authentication: JWT or session-based. Every billing endpoint requires a valid studio-level token and user identity.
  - Authorization: Role-based checks: only users with roles Owner or Billing/Finance Admin can mutate subscriptions/payment methods and view full invoice PDFs; other roles can view limited billing summary.
  - PCI and Payment Data: Never store raw card PAN/CVV on server. Use tokenization via payment provider. Store only providerPaymentMethodId, last4, brand and expiry.
  - Webhook verification: verify provider signature header and timestamp; reject if invalid.
  - Rate limiting: protect webhook endpoint and billing APIs.
  - Audit logging: store who performed subscription changes and payment method changes (userId, timestamp, IP).

- Validation:
  - planId: must be one of allowed values (enum).
  - seats: integer >= 1 and <= max allowed for plan.
  - promo code: validate format (alphanumeric, 4–32 chars) and expiry.
  - billing contact email: valid email format.
  - address fields: required fields per country when generating invoice PDFs (country, line1, city, postalCode).
  - payment provider tokens: follow provider-specified schema; backend will reject malformed tokens.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Billing page renders all cards (Current Plan, Pricing Tiers, Invoices, Payment Methods, Promo Codes, Billing Contact) according to visual spec with responsive behavior.
- [ ] Only authorized roles (Owner / Billing Admin) can add/remove payment methods and change subscription; attempt by others returns HTTP 403 and UI shows read-only state.
- [ ] Adding a payment method uses tokenization (no PAN/CVV stored) and POST /payment-methods returns stored payment method with last4/brand and can be set as default.
- [ ] Upgrading/downgrading subscription hits subscription endpoints and updates Subscription model; billing summary updates with new nextBillingDate or pro-rated notice.
- [ ] Invoice list displays accurate invoice statuses and allows downloading a PDF generated with the studio's branding.
- [ ] Webhook endpoint verifies provider signature and updates DB on invoice.payment_succeeded and payment_failed events.
- [ ] Promo codes can be applied; credits are reflected in billing summary and in next invoice calculation.
- [ ] All flows include clear success/error messaging and accessible modals, and pass basic accessibility checks (keyboard navigation, aria labels).

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:

- Use primary background #F7F7F9 for the page backdrop; card backgrounds #FFFFFF with very subtle shadow and border #E5E7EB.
- Accent actions and primary CTAs use #0052CC; disabled and secondary use neutral grays #D1D5DB and #6B7280.
- Status pills: active/success #10B981, warning #F59E42, error #EF4444.
- Typography: Inter or SF Pro. H1 28px bold (600–700), H2 22px, H3 18px. Body 15–16px.
- Layout: 12-column grid, 24–32px gutters/padding. Left-aligned content, large whitespace.
- Cards: 8–12px border-radius, title bold at top, secondary info muted gray, CTA aligned right.
- Sidebar: permanent vertical with active item highlighted. Topbar clean white with bottom border #E5E7EB.
- Buttons: Primary rounded rectangle #0052CC with white text, secondary ghost style. Provide hover/active/disabled states.
- Forms: rounded inputs with border #D1D5DB and clear focus ring.

Design details to implement:
- Seat usage progress bar: subtle gradient or accent for used portion; numeric label (e.g., "8 of 10 seats used").
- Pricing toggle (Monthly/Annual): a segmented control near Pricing Tiers with immediate price recalculation and savings indicator for annual.
- Invoice row hover: background tint #F3F4F6 and visible action icons.
- Payment method card: small chip with brand icon, last4, "Default" badge if primary.
- Confirm modals must show key billing implications (prorated charges or refunds), seat changes, and an estimated first invoice amount or charge.

Design Philosophy:
- Keep interface minimal and calm; prioritize clarity and quick scanning (prominent plan summary and CTAs).
- Use whitespace and typography to lower cognitive load; emphasize actions (upgrade/manage) with clear, accessible CTAs.

Additional Notes for the Developer / AI Tool:
- Implement feature flags to enable/disable payment provider integration during development and to switch between mock and real adapter.
- Provide mock data endpoints for frontend dev (mock payment provider tokens, mock invoices) and automated tests for each API endpoint and typical flows (add card, upgrade, webhook invoice paid).
- Provide unit and integration tests for key backend logic (promo application, invoice PDF generation, webhook verification).
- Document integration steps to swap in a real payment provider (Stripe/Chargebee/Braintree): required credentials, expected webhook events, mapping to adapter methods.
- Include sample invoice PDF template (HTML/CSS) using the specified visual style and the studio branding fields; expose preview in Settings > Branding panel.

This prompt is intended to be actionable by an AI dev tool or engineering team: it defines UI layout, components, API contracts, data models, security, validation rules, UX flows, design tokens, and acceptance criteria to implement a production-ready Billing & Pricing experience integrated with Studio Settings & Team Management for Archject. for style.

CRITICAL DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:
- You MUST follow ALL design principles and patterns specified in the Design Reference above
- Do NOT deviate from the design specifications without explicit user permission
- Implement ALL visual design elements (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, animations) as specified
- Follow the layout patterns and component designs exactly as documented
- Ensure all interactions and micro-animations match the reference specifications

CRITICAL TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:
- React 18.3.1, React Router 6.30.1
- Tailwind CSS v3 with tailwind.config.js and custom keyframes
- @tailwindcss/typography plugin for rich text content
- Tailwind CSS animations (NOT Motion library or framer-motion)
- Sonner for toasts
- Recharts for data visualization
- Native fetch() with API utilities in src/lib/api.ts
- Design system with CSS custom properties
- Use RGB color values for theming
- When Supabase is configured: use Edge Functions for LLM and server-only logic; never expose API keys in the client

=== TASK ===
# Billing & Pricing Page

## Overview
Build a complete, production-ready Billing & Pricing experience for Archject that displays current plan details, seat usage, invoices & receipts, payment methods, promo codes/credits, and upgrade/downgrade flows. Also implement a connected Settings & Team Management section at the studio level to manage branding, team roles, subscription settings, and integration links that tie into billing. The deliverable should include frontend UI, backend APIs, data models, security, validation, and integration instructions sufficient for an AI development tool or engineering team to implement end-to-end.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A single workspace area (accessible from the studio sidebar) where admins/owners view and manage their subscription and billing for Archject. It consolidates: current plan summary, upgrade/downgrade pricing tiers and comparisons, invoices and downloadable receipts, payment methods (securely add / remove / set default), promo code/credits application, and trial/upgrade CTA. It is tightly coupled with the Studio Settings & Team Management page for role-based access and branding (invoices, emails) and optionally with future payment provider integrations.

Goals:
- Provide transparent subscription information and clear upgrade/downgrade paths for studios.
- Allow secure management of payment methods and easy retrieval of historical invoices and receipts.
- Support promo codes and account credits, show seat counts and next billing date.
- Surface trial status and easy upgrade from trial to paid plans.
- Ensure branding and email template controls from Settings reflect on invoice PDFs and transactional emails.

Connected features:
- Settings & Team Management: for subscription ownership, billing contact, branding (logo on invoice), email templates and who can manage billing (roles).
- User roles & permissions system (only Owners/Finance/Admin can manage billing).
- Payment provider integration (placeholder now; exact provider TBD — implement a clean payment-provider adapter).
- Accounting export: invoice download (PDF/CSV) and transaction metadata for exports.

UI elements & visual guidance:
- Page layout follows project design system: left sidebar navigation, topbar, main content area on #F7F7F9 background, cards on #FFFFFF with subtle shadow and #E5E7EB borders.
- Key sections (each in a card):
  1. Current Plan Summary card: plan name, seats used/allocated, next billing date, billing cycle, per-seat cost (if applicable), status pill (active/trial/cancelled) in status colors. Right aligned primary CTA: Upgrade / Manage seats.
  2. Pricing Tiers card: Tier grid with comparison table (features rows, columns per tier), primary CTA per tier (Upgrade/Choose). Highlight current tier with accent color border.
  3. Invoices & Receipts card: searchable & paginated table/list with invoice number, date, amount, status (paid/failed/refunded), download invoice PDF button and a "View details" expand/collapse. Allow filter by year and export CSV.
  4. Payment Methods card: list of cards on file with brand icon, last4, expiration, default badge; Add Payment Method button (opens modal/stripe-hosted element or tokenized form). Remove with confirmation, set default flow.
  5. Promo Codes & Credits card: input to apply promo codes, list of active credits, credit balance, and UI that shows how credits are applied to next invoice.
  6. Billing Contact & Billing Address card: editable fields for billing email, company name, address — used to populate invoices. Save button and validation.
  7. Trial Status / Upgrade CTA banner: top area that shows trial remaining days and "Upgrade Now" button; or if past due, a warning state with restore payment CTA.

API integrations:
- Provide an abstract payment provider adapter layer for card tokenization, subscription management, invoice retrieval and webhooks. No concrete provider is mandated; design for Stripe-like APIs but keep adapter hooks documented so provider can be swapped.
- Email generation/invoice rendering: invoice PDFs generated server-side using invoice template that pulls studio branding from Settings (logo, color accent optionally) and billing contact data.
- Webhooks endpoint to receive payment events (invoice.paid, payment_failed, subscription_updated) from the payment provider. Webhook handler updates invoice and subscription records and notifies studio members as appropriate.

## Components to Build
1. BillingPage (main container)
   - Subcomponents: CurrentPlanCard, PricingTiersGrid, InvoicesList, PaymentMethodsList, PromoCreditsCard, BillingContactForm, TrialBanner.
2. BillingModals
   - AddPaymentMethodModal (hosted element/iframe option), ConfirmRemoveCardModal, UpgradeConfirmModal, ApplyPromoModal, InvoiceDetailModal.
3. Settings & Team Management Page (studio-level)
   - Subcomponents: BrandingPanel (logo upload, invoice template preview, email template editor), TeamRolesTable (invite/remove/edit roles/permissions), SubscriptionManagementPanel (link to BillingPage, list of subscriptions), IntegrationsPanel (connectors list with enable/disable).
4. Payment Provider Adapter
   - Interfaces: createPaymentMethod, attachPaymentMethodToCustomer, detachPaymentMethod, listPaymentMethods, createSubscription, updateSubscription, listInvoices, getInvoicePdf, applyCoupon/promo.
5. Backend Webhook Receiver & Queue Processor
   - Webhook routes, signature verification, event handlers that update DB and enqueue notification emails.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Tech stack expectations: React + TypeScript, component library alignment to design tokens (spacing, colors, typography). Use CSS-in-JS (styled-components/emotion) or Tailwind with a design token layer. All components fully responsive and accessible (WCAG AA).
- Pages/Routes:
  - /studio/:studioId/billing — Billing & Pricing Page (only accessible for studio admins/owners)
  - /studio/:studioId/settings/team — Settings & Team Management
- UI Elements & Interactions:
  - Current Plan Summary: small card with plan badge, seats usage progress bar (with percentage and numeric: e.g., 8/10 seats), next billing date, "Change plan" button.
  - Pricing Tiers: responsive three-column card layout for tiers (e.g., Free, Pro, Studio). Each tile shows price (monthly/annual toggle), key features, seat limits, CTA. Tier comparison modal displays a feature matrix.
  - Invoices Table: columns [Invoice #, Date, Amount, Status, Actions]. Actions: Download PDF, View details, Resend to billing email. Table supports search by invoice number, filter by year, and pagination.
  - Payment Methods: card list with brand icons; Add card uses secure provider element (PCI compliance). Mark a card as default; removal requires confirmation if default.
  - Promo Codes: free text input + Apply button; validates with backend and shows success/failure messaging. Show available credits and how many will be applied to next invoice.
  - Modals: accessible focus trap, close on ESC, labelled with aria attributes.
  - Notifications: success/error toasts on actions (apply promo, card added, invoice downloaded).
- Visual & micro-interactions: hover lifts, focus rings, disabled states; use defined palette and spacing.

### Backend
- Tech stack expectations: Node.js/TypeScript (Express or Fastify) or equivalent. Database relational (Postgres) or document store (Postgres recommended). Use migrations and typed models (Prisma/TypeORM).
- API surface:
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/billing — return aggregated billing summary (plan, seats, next billing date, trial status, credit balance).
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/invoices?year=&page=&perPage= — paginated invoices list.
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/invoices/:invoiceId/pdf — download PDF.
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods — create/attach payment method (accepts provider token).
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods — list payment methods.
  - DELETE /api/studios/:studioId/payment-methods/:methodId — detach method.
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/subscription — create or change subscription (payload: planId, seats, promoCode).
  - PATCH /api/studios/:studioId/subscription — change seats/plan.
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/promos/apply — validate and apply promo.
  - POST /api/studios/:studioId/billing/contact — update billing contact & address.
  - POST /webhooks/payment-provider — webhook entrypoint for payment provider events.
- Server functions:
  - Invoice PDF generation service (render invoice with studio branding).
  - Subscription lifecycle manager (create/update/cancel subscriptions).
  - Payment provider adapter / service (abstract layer with implementations).
  - Notification service (send billing emails using email templates from Branding settings).
  - Scheduler to create recurring invoices or reconcile failed payments (if provider doesn't auto-manage).
- Data retention & logs for audit: store transaction ids, provider event ids and raw payloads.

### Integration
- Payment provider adapter contract must be defined and used by subscription APIs. Implement a mock adapter for development and a Stripe-like adapter for production.
- Webhooks: verify signature header (provider-specific) and map events to local models. On invoice.payment_succeeded => mark invoice paid, notify billing email, store pdf link. On payment_failed => set subscription/pending state and notify owners.
- Branding: the invoice PDF generator must fetch studio branding (logo/secondary color and billing contact) from Settings. Email templates should be populated with invoice links and trial/plan details.
- Team Roles: Settings page manages who can access / manage billing. Enforce via backend authorization checks on every billing endpoint.

## User Experience Flow
1. Admin navigates to Studio > Billing.
2. Top banner shows trial status or active subscription summary with "Upgrade" CTA.
3. Admin reviews Current Plan card to confirm seats and next billing date.
4. Admin opens Pricing Tiers to compare options (monthly/annual toggle). Chooses a tier and clicks "Upgrade".
5. Upgrade flow:
   - If no payment method: prompt Add Payment Method modal (secure tokenized element). After adding, create subscription via backend adapter and show success toast.
   - If payment method exists: confirm upgrade modal showing pro-rated cost/next invoice. Confirm calls subscription API, updates DB, and redirects to success state.
6. Admin manages Payment Methods: adds/removes/toggles default. Removing default prompts to select alternative or shows warning.
7. Admin views Invoices list: filters and downloads PDF, or clicks "Resend invoice" to email billing contact.
8. Admin applies a promo code via Promo card and sees credits reflected immediately in Billing Summary; next invoice will show credit deduction.
9. Non-owner user without billing permission sees read-only billing summary and "Request change" button to contact Owners.
10. Any external payment events (webhooks) update subscription and invoice state in real time; UI reflects changes with notifications.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models:

Studio
- id: UUID
- name: string
- billingContactId: UUID -> BillingContact
- defaultCurrency: string (e.g., "USD")
- branding: { logoUrl: string, invoiceAccentColor?: string, invoiceTemplateId?: UUID }
- createdAt, updatedAt

BillingContact
- id: UUID
- studioId: UUID
- name: string
- email: string
- companyName?: string
- address: { line1, line2, city, state, postalCode, country }
- taxId?: string

Subscription
- id: UUID
- studioId: UUID
- providerSubscriptionId: string (provider-specific)
- planId: string (internal plan slug)
- seats: integer
- status: enum (active, trialing, canceled, past_due, unpaid)
- pricePerSeatCents: integer
- billingCycle: enum (monthly, annual)
- nextBillingDate: timestamp
- trialEndsAt?: timestamp
- createdAt, updatedAt

Invoice
- id: UUID
- studioId: UUID
- providerInvoiceId: string
- invoiceNumber: string
- amountDueCents: integer
- amountPaidCents: integer
- currency: string
- status: enum (draft, open, paid, void, failed)
- pdfUrl?: string or blob storage key
- issuedAt: timestamp
- dueAt?: timestamp
- lineItems: JSON array [{description, quantity, unitAmountCents}]
- rawProviderPayload: JSON
- createdAt, updatedAt

PaymentMethod
- id: UUID
- studioId: UUID
- providerPaymentMethodId: string
- brand: string (Visa, Mastercard)
- last4: string
- expMonth: int
- expYear: int
- isDefault: boolean
- createdAt, updatedAt

Promo / Credit
- id: UUID
- code: string
- studioId?: UUID (if single-use per studio)
- amountCents?: integer
- percentOff?: integer
- expiresAt?: timestamp
- isActive: boolean
- appliedToInvoiceIds: JSON array
- createdAt, updatedAt

WebhookEvents
- id: UUID
- providerEventId: string
- studioId?: UUID
- eventType: string
- payload: JSON
- receivedAt, processedAt, status

- API Endpoints: (all require Authorization: Bearer <token> and studio-level permission check)
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/billing [200] — returns consolidated billing summary (Subscription, credits, default payment method)
  - GET /api/studios/:studioId/subscription [200] — subscription details
